<i>Outpatient Department</i>

5
00:01:52,220 --> 00:01:52,960
<i>What are you doing?</i>

6
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:54,159
I'm in the store.

7
00:01:54,250 --> 00:01:55,189
What's up?

8
00:01:56,770 --> 00:01:57,680
<i>Nothing much.</i>

9
00:01:57,770 --> 00:01:58,560
<i>I just got off from work</i>

10
00:01:58,650 --> 00:01:59,830
<i>and thought I'd call you.</i>

11
00:02:00,409 --> 00:02:01,840
Miss, how much for these books?

12
00:02:01,930 --> 00:02:02,810
Hang on.

13
00:02:03,250 --> 00:02:04,330
Are you a member?

14
00:02:04,409 --> 00:02:04,840
Yes.

15
00:02:04,930 --> 00:02:06,440
<i>We have a four for eighty
promotion right now.</i>

16
00:02:06,530 --> 00:02:07,590
<i>We accept digital payment.</i>

17
00:02:09,810 --> 00:02:10,910
Please come again.

18
00:02:14,289 --> 00:02:15,349
How's business?

19
00:02:16,170 --> 00:02:17,200
<i>Pretty good.</i>

20
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:17,970
By the way,

21
00:02:18,050 --> 00:02:20,560
I organised a reading session
at the store

22
00:02:20,650 --> 00:02:22,120
based on movies.

23
00:02:22,210 --> 00:02:23,400
We had a pretty huge crowd.

24
00:02:23,490 --> 00:02:24,680
<i>The reception was fantastic.</i>

25
00:02:25,090 --> 00:02:25,890
<i>The zodiac bookmarks</i>

26
00:02:25,970 --> 00:02:27,750
I designed sold pretty well, too.

27
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:29,880
I'm thinking of doing

28
00:02:29,970 --> 00:02:31,600
zodiac themed

29
00:02:31,690 --> 00:02:34,040
hats, socks, t-shirts, and the like.

30
00:02:34,810 --> 00:02:36,190
<i>What's your zodiac?</i>

31
00:02:36,530 --> 00:02:38,229
<i>Wait, let me guess.</i>

32
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:39,840
It's...

33
00:02:39,930 --> 00:02:41,110
<i>Meng Zhen.</i>

34
00:02:43,210 --> 00:02:45,040
Let's have a meal this weekend.

35
00:02:45,970 --> 00:02:47,350
I'll come and fetch you and Xiao Jun.

36
00:02:51,860 --> 00:02:52,960
What's the occasion?

37
00:02:54,050 --> 00:02:55,430
I'd like to introduce you and Xiao Jun

38
00:02:56,170 --> 00:02:57,550
to my parents.

39
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,190
I want to announce to them

40
00:03:02,290 --> 00:03:03,670
<i>that you're my lover.</i>

41
00:03:07,770 --> 00:03:08,750
Sure.

42
00:03:09,890 --> 00:03:10,770
Alright.

43
00:03:11,210 --> 00:03:12,110
See you this weekend.

44
00:03:25,370 --> 00:03:26,310
Xiao Jun.

45
00:03:27,570 --> 00:03:28,450
Time for your medicine.

46
00:03:43,610 --> 00:03:44,490
All done?

47
00:03:46,930 --> 00:03:47,910
Mum.

48
00:03:51,770 --> 00:03:52,720
Yes?

49
00:03:52,810 --> 00:03:54,510
Actually, Zhang Yi Chi is alright.

50
00:03:56,690 --> 00:03:58,000
Why are you telling me this?

51
00:03:58,610 --> 00:04:00,310
He may not be athletic,

52
00:04:00,729 --> 00:04:02,229
but he has a brilliant mind.

53
00:04:02,729 --> 00:04:05,280
A woman should find a clever husband.

54
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:06,590
It'll save you a lot of trouble.

55
00:04:06,930 --> 00:04:08,560
What told you that?

56
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:09,670
It's true.

57
00:04:10,010 --> 00:04:11,870
That's what Xuan Xuan said.

58
00:04:12,930 --> 00:04:13,950
For her sake,

59
00:04:14,370 --> 00:04:16,790
I must work hard and become
a smart person.

60
00:04:16,970 --> 00:04:18,870
Good. You have my support.

61
00:04:19,330 --> 00:04:20,280
So

62
00:04:20,370 --> 00:04:22,549
it doesn't have to be Daddy Liang?

63
00:04:22,850 --> 00:04:24,410
Liang Mu Ze is my father.

64
00:04:24,489 --> 00:04:26,150
Zhang Yi Chi is your husband.

65
00:04:26,330 --> 00:04:27,049
There's no conflict.

66
00:04:27,130 --> 00:04:28,170
What do you mean "husband?"

67
00:04:28,260 --> 00:04:29,630
We're not even past first base.

68
00:04:29,930 --> 00:04:33,070
What are you thinking with that
little head of yours?

69
00:04:33,210 --> 00:04:34,790
About your happiness.

70
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:36,620
Okay.

71
00:04:36,970 --> 00:04:39,350
I'll try my best to lead a happy life.

72
00:04:39,450 --> 00:04:40,320
Alright?

73
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:41,290
Alright.

74
00:04:41,610 --> 00:04:42,550
Good boy.

75
00:04:45,890 --> 00:04:47,150
<i>Dr Xia,</i>

76
00:04:47,330 --> 00:04:48,760
<i>I don't know if I'll</i>

77
00:04:48,850 --> 00:04:50,870
<i>survive the infection.</i>

78
00:04:51,730 --> 00:04:52,950
<i>But there's something</i>

79
00:04:53,330 --> 00:04:54,630
<i>I must tell you.</i>

80
00:04:55,450 --> 00:04:56,830
<i>The truth is,</i>

81
00:04:57,170 --> 00:04:58,990
<i>I regretted my decision</i>

82
00:04:59,250 --> 00:05:00,720
<i>the moment I swallowed the pesticide.</i>

83
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:03,230
<i>I thought I would die for sure.</i>

84
00:05:04,050 --> 00:05:05,630
<i>Thank you for not giving up.</i>

85
00:05:06,330 --> 00:05:09,270
<i>You've prolonged my life.</i>

86
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:12,350
<i>I never was a brave person.</i>

87
00:05:12,450 --> 00:05:14,670
<i>But my father's passing reminded me</i>

88
00:05:15,250 --> 00:05:16,350
<i>that I must live on.</i>

89
00:05:16,930 --> 00:05:18,510
<i>Not just for myself,</i>

90
00:05:19,050 --> 00:05:21,390
<i>but for the sacrifices he made
for me.</i>

91
00:05:22,290 --> 00:05:24,600
<i>This ordeal at the age of 18
was too painful.</i>

92
00:05:25,130 --> 00:05:27,470
<i>Luckily, I was given a second chance.</i>

93
00:05:28,530 --> 00:05:29,670
<i>The gentle breeze.</i>

94
00:05:29,890 --> 00:05:30,790
<i>The warm sunlight.</i>

95
00:05:31,090 --> 00:05:32,530
<i>The scent of foliage.</i>

96
00:05:32,610 --> 00:05:33,360
<i>Even the most</i>

97
00:05:33,450 --> 00:05:35,790
<i>minute speckle of dust makes
me feel alive.</i>

98
00:05:36,530 --> 00:05:38,190
<i>If even for one day.</i>

99
00:05:38,530 --> 00:05:40,120
<i>One day is enough.</i>

100
00:05:40,780 --> 00:05:41,880
<i>Dr Xia,</i>

101
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:43,430
<i>thank you.</i>

102
00:05:43,770 --> 00:05:45,070
<i>Besides "thank you,"</i>

103
00:05:45,690 --> 00:05:47,390
<i>I don't know what else to say.</i>

104
00:05:47,690 --> 00:05:49,150
<i>Thank you.</i>

105
00:05:49,650 --> 00:05:51,270
<i>I have no regrets.</i>

106
00:06:29,450 --> 00:06:31,310
<i>Every patient steps into a hospital</i>

107
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:34,390
<i>with the hopes of getting better.</i>

108
00:06:35,140 --> 00:06:37,559
<i>And every doctor puts on her white coat</i>

109
00:06:37,890 --> 00:06:40,350
<i>with the belief that it is her duty
to cure them.</i>

110
00:06:41,090 --> 00:06:43,550
<i>In the brutal struggle
between life and death,</i>

111
00:06:44,450 --> 00:06:45,990
<i>the patient may be fragile,</i>

112
00:06:46,809 --> 00:06:48,950
<i>but the doctor must be strong.</i>

113
00:06:57,490 --> 00:06:58,830
<i>We fight against a common enemy,</i>

114
00:06:59,370 --> 00:07:01,030
<i>licking our bleeding wounds</i>

115
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:02,710
<i>in our respective ways.</i>

116
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:05,510
<i>We seek victory,</i>

117
00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:07,390
<i>but the possibility of defeat</i>

118
00:07:07,530 --> 00:07:09,030
<i>is ever-present.</i>

119
00:07:13,010 --> 00:07:14,830
<i>Life is full of vicissitudes.</i>

120
00:07:16,010 --> 00:07:17,470
<i>In the face of the light,</i>

121
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:19,510
<i>what is victory?</i>

122
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:22,270
<i>One must keep living.</i>

123
00:07:23,050 --> 00:07:24,150
<i>With courage</i>

124
00:07:24,490 --> 00:07:25,510
<i>and passion.</i>

125
00:07:37,809 --> 00:07:39,230
<i>Liu Ran passed away.</i>

126
00:08:20,730 --> 00:08:22,030
Have you met Old Master?

127
00:08:22,890 --> 00:08:24,270
Does he know about the merchandise?

128
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:25,950
He knew the moment it happened.

129
00:08:26,970 --> 00:08:28,190
And he didn't suspect you?

130
00:08:28,770 --> 00:08:30,110
If I had done it,

131
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:31,590
I wouldn't have had the nerve
to see him.

132
00:08:31,810 --> 00:08:32,910
That's what he probably thought.

133
00:08:34,290 --> 00:08:35,670
What's his next move?

134
00:08:36,570 --> 00:08:37,850
He'll let me know

135
00:08:37,939 --> 00:08:38,990
when the time comes.

136
00:08:39,490 --> 00:08:40,370
At least

137
00:08:40,730 --> 00:08:42,550
he hasn't shut me off.

138
00:08:43,170 --> 00:08:44,040
That risky move,

139
00:08:44,130 --> 00:08:46,230
whether for you or for me,

140
00:08:46,530 --> 00:08:47,750
was the right move.

141
00:08:48,329 --> 00:08:49,950
Whether it's the right move
doesn't depend on what you say

142
00:08:50,930 --> 00:08:52,030
but what you do.

143
00:08:53,850 --> 00:08:55,000
I get it.

144
00:08:55,130 --> 00:08:56,360
I'll cooperate with the cops

145
00:08:56,450 --> 00:08:57,910
from here on out.

146
00:08:58,570 --> 00:09:00,150
As long as I can save my mother.

147
00:09:01,650 --> 00:09:02,750
Good.

148
00:09:23,130 --> 00:09:24,110
How's your arm?

149
00:09:24,210 --> 00:09:25,270
Commander,

150
00:09:26,010 --> 00:09:26,990
it's still weak.

151
00:09:27,170 --> 00:09:28,710
Further check-up is required.

152
00:09:29,690 --> 00:09:30,710
Is that what the doctor said?

153
00:09:31,130 --> 00:09:32,710
I feel I should get it checked.

154
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:34,130
Right.

155
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,290
Go in the afternoon.

156
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:36,310
Yes, sir!

157
00:09:37,890 --> 00:09:39,290
The rest of you, go back
and recalibrate.

158
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:40,960
Then assemble at the canteen
for dinner.

159
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,930
Thank you, Commander.

160
00:09:43,390 --> 00:09:44,420
Dismissed.

161
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:46,140
Tian Yong!

162
00:09:46,230 --> 00:09:47,890
Tian Yong!

163
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:49,700
Tian Yong!

164
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:51,980
I knew it,

165
00:09:52,070 --> 00:09:53,170
you're back!

166
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:58,540
How did you know Tian Yong
was back?

167
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:00,970
Tarot cards.

168
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,350
You can tell the future
with tarot cards?

169
00:10:03,430 --> 00:10:04,390
Of course.

170
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,150
Look.

171
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,470
I have four cards here.

172
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,250
Each represents a question.

173
00:10:08,880 --> 00:10:10,010
Where is Tian Yong?

174
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:12,330
What is Tian Yong doing?

175
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:14,290
When is Tian Yong coming back?

176
00:10:15,680 --> 00:10:16,870
That's only three questions.

177
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:17,830
What's the last one?

178
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,110
Three and four are pretty
much the same.

179
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,940
How are they the same?

180
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,460
They're both single digits.

181
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:26,670
Okay.

182
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:27,230
Fine.

183
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,430
Let me ask you,

184
00:10:28,510 --> 00:10:30,930
how did you know Tian Yong was
coming back today?

185
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,330
Well,

186
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:36,430
I held my breath,

187
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:37,470
closed my eyes,

188
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:38,660
and put my hands together.

189
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,110
Focusing my gaze on the card,

190
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,930
I asked my question.

191
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,430
The thoughts in my mind

192
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:45,570
coalesce in a confusion of magnetic waves.

193
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,060
Then suddenly,

194
00:10:48,430 --> 00:10:49,630
I heard your wife

195
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:51,580
coming downstairs with a soldier's wife.

196
00:10:51,680 --> 00:10:53,420
They said you were coming
back today.

197
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,460
After all that hocus pocus,

198
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:58,580
turns out you got it from someone else?

199
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,910
What does it have to do with tarot cards?

200
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,050
Nothing.

201
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:04,860
Then why did you bring out
the tarot cards?

202
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,030
Foreshadowing.

203
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,510
It's a performance device
in ancient oral literature.

204
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:11,270
The tarot cards are meant to
arouse the audience's interest

205
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:13,660
and serve as a prelude to
the main message.

206
00:11:16,350 --> 00:11:17,810
You scared me.

207
00:11:21,870 --> 00:11:22,820
Commander.

208
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,300
Quit talking nonsense.

209
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:30,660
What's it to you?

210
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:32,110
Easy there.

211
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,300
Are you injured?

212
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,300
Keep an eye on her.

213
00:11:36,390 --> 00:11:37,270
Yes.

214
00:11:37,950 --> 00:11:39,660
How did my brother get injured?

215
00:11:46,630 --> 00:11:48,980
What do you think of my
foreshadowing?

216
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,580
Don't hit your brother so hard next time.

217
00:11:58,860 --> 00:11:59,900
Let's go.

218
00:12:05,550 --> 00:12:07,330
Commander, I'll send her home
right now.

219
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:09,790
Is it just me

220
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:11,420
or am I getting old?

221
00:12:12,910 --> 00:12:13,670
I couldn't understand a word

222
00:12:13,760 --> 00:12:15,300
your cousin was saying.

223
00:12:16,230 --> 00:12:17,890
Oh no. I don't get her, either.

224
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,410
Neither does the rest of my family.

225
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:20,800
Really?

226
00:12:22,160 --> 00:12:23,930
You said Tian Yong

227
00:12:24,150 --> 00:12:25,490
is not compatible with your cousin.

228
00:12:25,710 --> 00:12:26,860
Indeed,

229
00:12:27,110 --> 00:12:29,140
Tang Yong is an ancient literature buff.

230
00:12:29,310 --> 00:12:31,290
If the two of them get together,

231
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,410
they'd have trouble communicating.

232
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,490
They're not right for each other.

233
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:37,340
Not necessarily, Commander.

234
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:39,860
Of all the ways youngsters
communicate today,

235
00:12:40,280 --> 00:12:42,090
language is the least significant.

236
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:43,630
Really?

237
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,260
Isn't that a good thing?

238
00:12:47,710 --> 00:12:48,660
Yeah.

239
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:51,700
I still don't get it.

240
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:58,490
Why are you still here?

241
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:00,180
To keep you company.

242
00:13:03,230 --> 00:13:04,410
Don't you find the camp boring?

243
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,580
It is boring.

244
00:13:07,190 --> 00:13:08,460
So why don't you go?

245
00:13:09,910 --> 00:13:10,900
Because I want to keep
you company.

246
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,290
This mission

247
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,780
is very dangerous, isn't it?

248
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:21,610
No.

249
00:13:21,910 --> 00:13:22,860
You're lying.

250
00:13:23,340 --> 00:13:25,170
My brother hasn't had
an injury in ages.

251
00:13:27,830 --> 00:13:28,720
Did you guys

252
00:13:29,590 --> 00:13:30,770
kill?

253
00:13:32,550 --> 00:13:33,730
What did it feel like?

254
00:13:35,710 --> 00:13:37,560
"A hundred battles have worn
my armour down."

255
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:39,440
"Yet I won't return until
the enemy is defeated."

256
00:13:40,710 --> 00:13:42,010
Wang Chang Ling's

257
00:13:43,060 --> 00:13:44,850
"Conquering the Distant City,"

258
00:13:45,430 --> 00:13:46,530
poem four of seven?

259
00:13:48,310 --> 00:13:49,250
That's right.

260
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:51,340
You know something?

261
00:13:51,420 --> 00:13:52,850
While you were gone,

262
00:13:52,940 --> 00:13:55,130
I've been poring over that book
you gave me.

263
00:13:55,790 --> 00:13:57,460
For a girl of 21,

264
00:13:57,550 --> 00:13:59,370
memorising 300 Tang poems

265
00:13:59,590 --> 00:14:01,050
is a great feat.

266
00:14:01,980 --> 00:14:02,930
You've worked hard.

267
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:05,250
Then there's my AMBD.

268
00:14:05,620 --> 00:14:06,500
What's that?

269
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:09,680
You know ADHD?

270
00:14:10,190 --> 00:14:11,070
Yes.

271
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:13,330
If left untreated

272
00:14:13,420 --> 00:14:15,280
until adolescence,

273
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:17,130
it'll become what's known as

274
00:14:17,380 --> 00:14:19,920
autoimmune mucocutaneous
blistering disease.

275
00:14:30,790 --> 00:14:31,730
You mean

276
00:14:34,190 --> 00:14:35,370
something's wrong with your brain?

