00:35:11,900 --> 00:35:13,520
But you do.

565
00:35:14,020 --> 00:35:15,330
If he could hang up on you

566
00:35:15,420 --> 00:35:17,130
at the sound of my voice,

567
00:35:17,220 --> 00:35:18,130
is he any different

568
00:35:18,220 --> 00:35:20,260
from the Zhuo Ran who
abandoned you eight years ago?

569
00:35:20,340 --> 00:35:21,610
Do you want to make the
same mistake again?

570
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:22,720
Enough!

571
00:35:24,220 --> 00:35:24,810
Let me send you home.

572
00:35:24,900 --> 00:35:26,050
No, I'll walk.

573
00:35:26,140 --> 00:35:27,200
Calm down.

574
00:35:28,900 --> 00:35:30,050
I'm very calm right now.

575
00:35:30,270 --> 00:35:32,060
It's you who's too presumptuous.

576
00:35:32,150 --> 00:35:33,040
Look,

577
00:35:33,140 --> 00:35:34,140
when you left,

578
00:35:34,230 --> 00:35:34,970
I was a little fazed

579
00:35:35,060 --> 00:35:36,370
by the loss

580
00:35:36,460 --> 00:35:37,730
of an old friend at first

581
00:35:37,820 --> 00:35:39,860
and went through a rough patch.

582
00:35:39,950 --> 00:35:41,400
But later, I enrolled
in the Military Medical University

583
00:35:41,900 --> 00:35:43,170
and made many new friends.

584
00:35:43,260 --> 00:35:44,260
Studying, dating,

585
00:35:44,350 --> 00:35:45,210
extracurriculars,

586
00:35:45,300 --> 00:35:46,600
I did it all.

587
00:35:46,740 --> 00:35:48,290
I got by just fine.

588
00:35:48,380 --> 00:35:49,850
I wasn't as pathetic as you thought.

589
00:35:49,940 --> 00:35:50,930
I'm not some lovesick damsel

590
00:35:51,020 --> 00:35:52,180
waiting for your rescue.

591
00:35:52,270 --> 00:35:52,740
I won't give up

592
00:35:52,830 --> 00:35:54,440
just because my first relationship failed.

593
00:35:54,660 --> 00:35:55,330
Not in the past,

594
00:35:55,420 --> 00:35:56,140
not now,

595
00:35:56,230 --> 00:35:57,360
not ever.

596
00:35:57,980 --> 00:35:59,080
As for Liang Mu Ze,

597
00:36:01,310 --> 00:36:02,410
I love him.

598
00:36:09,380 --> 00:36:10,410
If he takes your "hi"

599
00:36:10,500 --> 00:36:11,450
the wrong way,

600
00:36:11,540 --> 00:36:12,610
and things don't work out,

601
00:36:12,700 --> 00:36:14,680
it doesn't mean you and I
will go back to the way we were.

602
00:36:15,100 --> 00:36:16,640
The past is in the past.

603
00:36:16,740 --> 00:36:18,530
I've moved on from my
18-year-old life.

604
00:36:18,620 --> 00:36:19,370
Even if it wasn't perfect,

605
00:36:19,460 --> 00:36:20,960
I don't want to live it again.

606
00:36:21,300 --> 00:36:22,420
I live for the present

607
00:36:22,500 --> 00:36:23,680
and the future.

608
00:36:24,190 --> 00:36:25,200
My relationships

609
00:36:25,340 --> 00:36:26,620
should be decided by me,

610
00:36:26,700 --> 00:36:28,370
not you.

611
00:36:28,590 --> 00:36:29,600
The reason I came here

612
00:36:29,980 --> 00:36:31,170
is to make myself clear

613
00:36:31,260 --> 00:36:32,960
to you once and for all.

614
00:36:33,780 --> 00:36:34,880
Do you understand?

615
00:36:55,820 --> 00:36:57,600
Liang... Liang Mu Ze.

616
00:36:57,870 --> 00:36:59,120
What are you doing here?

617
00:37:00,140 --> 00:37:01,360
I'm here to fetch you.

618
00:37:07,820 --> 00:37:08,760
Let's go.

619
00:37:27,700 --> 00:37:29,120
But we haven't gotten
to the eel rice yet.

620
00:37:29,860 --> 00:37:31,650
It's your favourite, Xia Chu.

621
00:37:33,740 --> 00:37:35,320
I no longer like eel rice.

622
00:37:36,150 --> 00:37:37,440
Please let go of me.

623
00:37:47,710 --> 00:37:48,840
In that case,

624
00:37:49,660 --> 00:37:51,720
we'll go back to our normal lives.

625
00:38:08,900 --> 00:38:10,400
When did you come back?

626
00:38:11,900 --> 00:38:13,640
Did you see my message?

627
00:38:16,260 --> 00:38:18,200
Can you slow down, Liang Mu Ze?

628
00:38:21,060 --> 00:38:22,160
Liang Mu Ze.

629
00:38:27,660 --> 00:38:29,240
I know you're mad at me.

630
00:38:30,070 --> 00:38:32,240
You didn't like me meeting up
with Zhuo Ran, did you?

631
00:38:33,940 --> 00:38:35,020
Don't deny it.

632
00:38:35,100 --> 00:38:36,680
I know that's what you're thinking.

633
00:38:41,860 --> 00:38:43,480
You're hurting my hand.

634
00:38:46,180 --> 00:38:47,320
I met up with him

635
00:38:48,140 --> 00:38:50,120
not because I couldn't
get over him

636
00:38:50,260 --> 00:38:51,970
but because I did.

637
00:38:52,190 --> 00:38:53,370
I wanted to set the record straight

638
00:38:53,460 --> 00:38:54,840
so he would let go, too.

639
00:38:55,900 --> 00:38:57,200
In any case,

640
00:38:58,300 --> 00:39:00,600
I loved him before.

641
00:39:02,310 --> 00:39:03,560
Since we came together on good terms,

642
00:39:04,860 --> 00:39:06,320
we should part ways on good terms.

643
00:39:07,390 --> 00:39:08,880
Because we may never
see each other again.

644
00:39:10,660 --> 00:39:12,240
Do you understand, Liang Mu Ze?

645
00:39:14,540 --> 00:39:16,410
Do you understand, Liang Mu Ze?

646
00:39:22,820 --> 00:39:24,660
Why don't we go to this restaurant?

647
00:39:24,740 --> 00:39:25,340
Sure.

648
00:39:25,430 --> 00:39:26,360
Why is she on the ground?

649
00:39:26,500 --> 00:39:27,440
Are they having a fight?

650
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:29,640
Don't mind them.

651
00:39:30,900 --> 00:39:32,000
Get up.

652
00:39:32,500 --> 00:39:34,960
I can't walk. I don't want to walk.

653
00:39:37,460 --> 00:39:39,480
Liu Ran passed away, do you know that?

654
00:39:40,860 --> 00:39:42,680
The lung transplant was a success,

655
00:39:43,220 --> 00:39:45,400
but the infection got to her.

656
00:39:46,500 --> 00:39:48,160
All the doctors

657
00:39:49,190 --> 00:39:51,450
stood by and watched her
drift into sleep.

658
00:39:51,540 --> 00:39:52,650
There was nothing they could do.

659
00:39:52,740 --> 00:39:54,160
Nothing.

660
00:39:54,260 --> 00:39:56,320
It was totally hopeless.

661
00:39:57,380 --> 00:39:58,330
Don't cry.

662
00:40:00,100 --> 00:40:01,100
Have you any idea

663
00:40:01,190 --> 00:40:03,000
what I've been through
the last few days?

664
00:40:04,740 --> 00:40:05,820
I was so sleepy

665
00:40:05,900 --> 00:40:07,020
but I couldn't sleep.

666
00:40:07,100 --> 00:40:09,360
I kept seeing her in my dreams.

667
00:40:09,620 --> 00:40:11,130
She even thanked me,

668
00:40:11,220 --> 00:40:12,570
as if I deserved it.

669
00:40:12,660 --> 00:40:14,090
I couldn't help her.

670
00:40:14,180 --> 00:40:15,680
I couldn't do a thing.

671
00:40:17,340 --> 00:40:19,780
Being a doctor is so hard.

672
00:40:19,860 --> 00:40:21,660
Everything is one big confusion.

673
00:40:21,740 --> 00:40:23,090
It's so tiresome.

674
00:40:30,820 --> 00:40:31,960
There, there.

675
00:40:33,300 --> 00:40:34,130
Come.

676
00:40:34,220 --> 00:40:35,320
Get up.

677
00:40:40,620 --> 00:40:41,500
Why?

678
00:40:42,260 --> 00:40:43,610
You said you couldn't walk.

679
00:40:43,700 --> 00:40:44,960
I'll carry you on my back.

680
00:40:46,940 --> 00:40:48,080
Are you sure?

681
00:40:48,180 --> 00:40:49,240
Come on.

682
00:40:59,460 --> 00:41:00,360
Is something wrong?

683
00:41:00,830 --> 00:41:02,600
Nothing. You're a little heavy,
that's all.

684
00:41:07,940 --> 00:41:09,640
Just kidding. Hold tight.

685
00:41:10,340 --> 00:41:11,290
Hold tight.

686
00:41:23,420 --> 00:41:24,650
You have a stubble.

687
00:41:24,740 --> 00:41:26,160
It's time to shave.

688
00:41:26,500 --> 00:41:27,800
I'll do it when I get back.

689
00:41:29,580 --> 00:41:31,000
Your ears are red.

690
00:41:33,140 --> 00:41:34,200
They're freezing.

691
00:41:34,830 --> 00:41:36,240
Let me blow on them.

692
00:41:40,420 --> 00:41:41,520
That's enough.

693
00:42:01,500 --> 00:42:03,090
I see so many documentaries

694
00:42:03,180 --> 00:42:04,340
of this calibre every year.

695
00:42:04,430 --> 00:42:05,050
They're all

696
00:42:05,140 --> 00:42:06,300
too dramatic.

697
00:42:06,380 --> 00:42:07,640
There's no subtlety.

698
00:42:08,260 --> 00:42:09,640
What do you think?

699
00:42:10,670 --> 00:42:14,280
<i>Zhuo Ran</i>

700
00:42:17,840 --> 00:42:20,400
Perhaps the closer I am
to their lives,

701
00:42:20,530 --> 00:42:22,400
the hardest it is for me to take
an objective view.

702
00:42:23,150 --> 00:42:24,130
Amateur.

703
00:42:28,220 --> 00:42:29,440
What did you say?

704
00:42:31,220 --> 00:42:32,840
She said you're very honest.

705
00:42:34,260 --> 00:42:35,200
That's right.

706
00:42:41,910 --> 00:42:43,800
<i>Zhuo Ran</i>

707
00:42:45,660 --> 00:42:47,520
Excuse me, I have to
take a call.

708
00:43:04,540 --> 00:43:06,050
Zhuo Ran, listen here.

709
00:43:06,620 --> 00:43:08,380
I'm having a gathering with my friends.

710
00:43:08,460 --> 00:43:10,570
I have my own life and career.

711
00:43:10,860 --> 00:43:12,170
I can't be at your beck and call

712
00:43:12,260 --> 00:43:13,100
24-7.

713
00:43:13,180 --> 00:43:14,290
I'm not some maid

714
00:43:14,380 --> 00:43:15,850
that you can order around at will.

715
00:43:17,980 --> 00:43:19,880
I detest this kind of relationship.

716
00:43:21,580 --> 00:43:22,760
Say something.

717
00:43:23,780 --> 00:43:25,760
<i>Every saint has a past.</i>

718
00:43:26,380 --> 00:43:28,000
<i>Every sinner has a future.</i>

719
00:43:28,860 --> 00:43:29,970
<i>Isn't that right,</i>

720
00:43:30,060 --> 00:43:30,940
<i>Mi Gu?</i>

721
00:43:31,340 --> 00:43:32,360
What's with you?

722
00:43:33,860 --> 00:43:34,900
Why are you telling me this?

723
00:43:34,980 --> 00:43:36,040
<i>I'm in the hotel.</i>

724
00:43:37,220 --> 00:43:38,100
<i>Are you coming?</i>

725
00:43:38,380 --> 00:43:39,440
No.

726
00:43:40,460 --> 00:43:41,890
My party has just started.

727
00:43:41,980 --> 00:43:43,120
<i>I'll be waiting for you.</i>

728
00:44:00,060 --> 00:44:01,720
Had your phone call?

729
00:44:04,900 --> 00:44:06,040
Yes.

730
00:44:08,860 --> 00:44:11,440
By the way, we just broke out
a bottle of wine.

731
00:44:12,500 --> 00:44:13,680
It's pretty good.

732
00:44:14,070 --> 00:44:15,640
Shall we go inside and taste it?

733
00:44:19,980 --> 00:44:20,960
Come on.

734
00:44:25,300 --> 00:44:26,490
No, thanks.

735
00:44:30,500 --> 00:44:31,570
You guys go ahead.

736
00:45:34,020 --> 00:45:35,050
You came.

737
00:45:37,100 --> 00:45:38,360
Why didn't you turn on the lights?

738
00:45:43,750 --> 00:45:44,920
I don't feel like it.

739
00:46:01,790 --> 00:46:02,720
What's wrong?

740
00:46:04,060 --> 00:46:05,280
Why are you drinking so heavily?

741
00:46:30,920 --> 00:46:32,940
I thought I had to wait all night for you.

742
00:46:33,880 --> 00:46:35,180
Was the party fun?

743
00:46:37,120 --> 00:46:38,260
Sure.

744
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:03,340
A group of beautiful, intelligent
men and women,

745
00:47:04,840 --> 00:47:07,220
sipping their
ten-thousand-dollar-a-bottle wine,

746
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:09,620
musing over

747
00:47:09,760 --> 00:47:11,140
topics of social justice

748
00:47:11,480 --> 00:47:13,020
and equality.

749
00:47:13,680 --> 00:47:16,780
They pretend to stand up
for the underprivileged.

750
00:47:18,320 --> 00:47:19,420
But I assure you,

751
00:47:20,200 --> 00:47:21,180
those people

752
00:47:21,680 --> 00:47:23,470
haven't the slightest clue

753
00:47:23,560 --> 00:47:24,500
what life is really like.

754
00:47:28,200 --> 00:47:29,430
Not once have they

755
00:47:29,520 --> 00:47:31,220
considered stepping out of

756
00:47:32,800 --> 00:47:34,020
the extravagant,

757
00:47:34,870 --> 00:47:35,860
highly intellectual,

758
00:47:36,880 --> 00:47:38,230
cultural elitist,

759
00:47:38,320 --> 00:47:41,020
and socially superior little bubble.

760
00:47:42,560 --> 00:47:43,820
I watched them

761
00:47:45,080 --> 00:47:47,220
descend into their own
self-indulgent world,

762
00:47:50,520 --> 00:47:52,740
their faces immaculate and pompous.

763
00:47:54,430 --> 00:47:55,580
Do you think it was fun?

